<plot>Angry Kid and his kid sister are sitting in the back seat of the family car as dad motors down the highway. An ambulance passes them and the Kid asks his dad why "ambulance" is spelled backwards on the front of the vehicle. As his dad explains, the Kid's sister spells out "daddy" backwards and holds it up for dad to see in the rear-view mirror. Pop is impressed, and the Kid gets a tad miffed at his sister's cleverness, so he starts in with how own backward writing. Soon it's two against one, or is it eno tsniaga owt?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?055668</url></doc>
